section#venue(full-height): .page-size

    img.header-illustrator(src='/assets/illustrations/venue.svg')

    h2.center Venue - The Barbican Centre
    p.center: strong
      | Silk Street London, EC2Y 8DS

    .row

        .col-7.copy
            p Welcome to the Barbican, Europe's largest multi-arts and conference venue presenting a diverse range of art, music, theatre, dance, film and creative learning events.

            h4 Tube
            p: strong Barbican, St Paul’s, Moorgate

            p The Barbican Centre is located within walking distance from Barbican, St Paul’s and Moorgate.

            h4 Rail

            p The nearest train stations are Liverpool Street and Farringdon.

            h4 Bus

            p Bus Route 153 runs directly past the Barbican along Chiswell Street.

            h4 Bycicle

            p Our nearest TFL bike station is&nbsp;
              a(href='https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/cycling/santander-cycles/find-a-docking-station', target='_blank') Silk Street.
                | Cycle racks are available at the entrance to&nbsp;
                a(href='https://www.barbican.org.uk/visitor-information/car-parking', target='_blank') Car Park 5
                | and exit to&nbsp;
                a(href='https://www.barbican.org.uk/visitor-information/car-parking', target='_blank') Car Park 3&nbsp;
                | and helmets and equipment can be left in our free cloakrooms.

        .col-5.center

